DTSTART:20260412T200000Z
DTEND:20260412T220000Z
LOCATION:Auer Hall &amp\; LIVE@jacobs
SUMMARY:Baroque Orchestra ŌĆō Ingrid Matthews\, director
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy this performance from almost anywhere in the world viaL
 IVE@jacobs!Repertoire to be announcedAbout the DirectorIngrid Matthews is
  professor of practice in historical performance (baroque violin) at the 
 Indiana University Jacobs School of Music. A graduate of IU\, where she s
 tudied with Josef Gingold and Stanley Ritchie\, Matthews is one of today'
 s most respected baroque violinists. Since winning first prize in the Erw
 in Bodky International Competition for Early Music in 1989\, she has appe
 ared as soloist\, guest director\, chamber musician\, and concertmaster w
 ith leading early music ensembles\, including the New York Collegium\, Au
 stralian Brandenburg Orchestra\, Boston Early Music Festival Orchestra\, 
 Ars Lyrica (Houston)\, Tafelmusik Baroque Orchestra (Toronto)\, Musica Pa
 cifica (San Francisco)\, and many others. Matthews cofounded the Seattle 
 Baroque Orchestra in 1994 and served as its music director until 2013. Ma
 tthews has won high critical acclaim for her extensive discography. Her r
 ecording J. S. Bach: Complete Sonatas and Partitas for Violin was named "
 top recommendation for this music ŌĆ” on either period or modern instrume
 nts" by American Record Guide. She also plays jazz and swing styles and i
 s active as a visual artist. Meeting URL: https://liveatjacobs.music.indi
 ana.edu/
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><strong>Enjoy this performance from almos
 t anywhere in the world via</strong><a href="https://liveatjacobs.music.i
 ndiana.edu/"><strong>LIVE@jacobs</strong></a><strong>!</strong><br /><br 
 /><em>Repertoire to be announced</em><br /><br /><strong>About the Direct
 or</strong><br /><br /><strong>Ingrid Matthews</strong> is professor of p
 ractice in historical performance (baroque violin) at the Indiana Univers
 ity Jacobs School of Music. A graduate of IU\, where she studied with Jos
 ef Gingold and Stanley Ritchie\, Matthews is one of today's most respecte
 d baroque violinists. Since winning first prize in the Erwin Bodky Intern
 ational Competition for Early Music in 1989\, she has appeared as soloist
 \, guest director\, chamber musician\, and concertmaster with leading ear
 ly music ensembles\, including the New York Collegium\, Australian Brande
 nburg Orchestra\, Boston Early Music Festival Orchestra\, Ars Lyrica (Hou
 ston)\, Tafelmusik Baroque Orchestra (Toronto)\, Musica Pacifica (San Fra
 ncisco)\, and many others. Matthews cofounded the Seattle Baroque Orchest
 ra in 1994 and served as its music director until 2013. Matthews has won 
 high critical acclaim for her extensive discography. Her recording <em>J.
  S. Bach: Complete Sonatas and Partitas for Violin</em> was named "top re
 commendation for this music ŌĆ” on either period or modern instruments" b
 y <em>American Record Guide</em>. She also plays jazz and swing styles an
 d is active as a visual artist.<br /></p> Meeting URL: https://liveatjaco
 bs.music.indiana.edu/
